FINAL: {"ResponseMetadata": {"RequestId": "49a261b7-0595-4dcf-ac24-c047ab5a368d", "HTTPStatusCode": 200, "HTTPHeaders": {"date": "Sat, 04 Jul 2026 13:44:50 GMT", "content-type": "application/json", "content-length": "1478", "connection": "keep-alive", "x-amzn-requestid": "49a261b7-0595-4dcf-ac24-c047ab5a368d"}, "RetryAttempts": 0}, "output": {"message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"text": "Based on the information in the search results, here are the key details about the Golden Time project:\n\n- The developer of the Golden Time website project is Marvin Ramoda. \n- Marvin Ramoda is collaborating with either Yoshiyuki Kodama or Taro Murakami as the clients for the project.\n- The primary objective is to create an end-to-end system where health and fitness enthusiasts can create and consume content related to topics like food supplements and fitness activities. Users will also be able to interact with content creators through commenting and reviews.\n- The scope of work includes developing web pages for desktop and mobile, implementing features like authentication, content management, commenting, and real-time/asynchronous content updates.\n- The project involves architecting the backend infrastructure and database schemas, as well as developing the API endpoints.\n- The project timeline is from November 6, 2023 to May 5, 2024, with regular testing, quality assurance, and communication between the developer and clients.\n- Success metrics include adherence to timeline, quality of code, and overall satisfaction of the clients.\n\nLet me know if you need any clarification or have additional questions about the Golden Time project details."}]}}, "stopReason": "end_turn", "usage": {"inputTokens": 3133, "outputTokens": 269, "totalTokens": 3402}, "metrics": {"latencyMs": 3568}}
CONTENT: Based on the information in the search results, here are the key details about the Golden Time project:

- The developer of the Golden Time website project is Marvin Ramoda. 
- Marvin Ramoda is collaborating with either Yoshiyuki Kodama or Taro Murakami as the clients for the project.
- The primary objective is to create an end-to-end system where health and fitness enthusiasts can create and consume content related to topics like food supplements and fitness activities. Users will also be able to interact with content creators through commenting and reviews.
- The scope of work includes developing web pages for desktop and mobile, implementing features like authentication, content management, commenting, and real-time/asynchronous content updates.
- The project involves architecting the backend infrastructure and database schemas, as well as developing the API endpoints.
- The project timeline is from November 6, 2023 to May 5, 2024, with regular testing, quality assurance, and communication between the developer and clients.
- Success metrics include adherence to timeline, quality of code, and overall satisfaction of the clients.

Let me know if you need any clarification or have additional questions about the Golden Time project details.
